Unity Post Processing Stack

*Playing with Tones and Effects of scene

- Unity offers an interface that allows access to visuals for game.

- Go to Asset Store -> Search for Post Processing Stack and download for free and import.

- In Projects search bar search for 'PostProcessingBehaviour'
(NOT PostProcessingBehaviourEditor)

- Drag and Drop onto the Main Camera

- Click on Main Camera -> in the Inspector the 'PostProcessingBehaviour' should be added, but it should have no 'Profile'

- In Assets -> PostProcessing Right click and hover over create -> find and click on 'create post-processing profile'

- Drag and drop this on to the 'Profile' slot in the Inspector for Main Camera
